	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>NES-Joint in reverse? 72-&gt;60 pins. Is this possible?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Would it be possible to solder a 72 pin connector from a Game Genie to the NES side of a NES Joint board, and plug it into a Famicom (without the female to female 60 pin part, of course) and use it as an adapter to play NES carts on the FC? Or am I just nuts? I've got a broke down Genie, and could easily grab up another Joint, but I thought I would ask first.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
