	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES-Joint in reverse? 72-&gt;60 pins. Is this possible?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The end of a joint is reverse in orientation to what you need for a socket.<br /><br />Ready-made Famicom&lt;-&gt;NES adapters are <a href="http://gamedoctorhk.com/index.php?main_page=product_info&amp;cPath=72_1_8_140&amp;products_id=1571" class="postlink">pretty cheap</a> anyway.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


