	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>infiniteneslives</b> [ Mon Dec 10, 2012 9:31 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES-Joint in reverse? 72-&gt;60 pins. Is this possible?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">&quot;(not included 3D function Nes game)&quot;<br /><br />What does this mean? Does it mean WorldRunner won't run? Rad Racer won't race?</div><br /><br />I presume they mean 4screen mirroring.  I've got one, seems to work well enough.<br /><br />But yes the adapter already (worthlessly) has CHR /A13 and CIRAM /CE tied together.  Additionally it has sound in and out tied together.  So if you had a NES cart with expansion sound, this adapter drops that sound when trying to run on the famicom.  This makes a little more sense though, since you can't rely on the NES cart to resolve the connectoring like they *could* have for mirroring.<br /><br />If you're already looking at doing that much hacking around with a game genie, modding this to work with 4screen mirroring and full sound would be cake.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


